{
  "id": "the_wardstone_in_the_wood",
  "encounterTitle": "Wardstone in the Wood",
  "description": "A wooded clearing under thick canopy. A dirt path runs north to south. To the right of the path is a wardstone with braziers.",
  "mapId": "the_wardstone_in_the_wood",
  "npcIds": [
    "goblin_minion",
    "goblin_minion"
  ],
  "allyIds": [],
  "enemyIds": [],
  "customIntroduction": "The forest trail is older than the road that replaced it, and the trees lean close. Half a mile in, the first wardstone stands where Bram said it would: a waist-high pillar of grey rock, its binding-glyph cracked clean through, the two halves leaning apart like a broken tooth. You've only ever seen that glyph drawn in a book. The air around it is cold and wrong — and the scuffed leaf-litter says you are not the first here, nor the only one now.",
  "customContext": "WOODLAND CLEARING — EXPLORATION then COMBAT. Reed enters from the western trail; the cracked wardstone stands at the clearing's centre, and the trail east continues toward the gorge bridge. Exploration comes FIRST — she examines the stone freely before anything moves. Three secrets reward searching (the engine runs the checks): Arcana/History DC 12 on the glyph reads the crack as structural decay, not sabotage — the ward rotted from within; Perception DC 10 on the scuffed litter finds fresh boot- and claw-tracks into the NE scrub; Perception DC 12 at the stone's base uncovers a healing vial cached by a Cape who never came back. Following the tracks into the NE scrub disturbs the nest: two goblin scavengers — opportunists after salvage, not soldiers. This is Reed's first real fight: keep it survivable but real, and reward a player who picks her ground before springing it. On victory the stone can't be mended here (the rite needs the keystone) — note it, salvage, and take the dry road east to the bridge.",
  "objective": "Examine the cracked wardstone, deal with what it drew from the moor, then follow the trail east.",
  "completionFlag": "wardstone_one_cleared",
